questionText:
People are given a maximum of six hours to complete a puzzle. The time spent on the puzzle, in hours, can be modelled using the continuous random variable X which has probability density function
f(x) = {Ax/(x² + 4), for 0 ≤ x ≤ 6 (where A > 0); 0, for all other values of x}

(a) Show that A = 2/ln 10.

sampleAnswer:
CDF: F(x) = ∫₀ˣ (1 − t/2) dt = [t − t²/4]₀ˣ = x − x²/4
F(x) = { 0, for x < 0; x − x²/4, for 0 ≤ x ≤ 2; 1, for x > 2 }
Graph starts at 0, increases with concave-down shape to reach 1 at x = 2.

questionText:
A continuous random variable X has a probability density function given by
f(x) = { 0 for x < 1, 1/x for 1 ≤ x ≤ e, 0 for x > e }

(a) Find the mode of the given probability density function. Justify your answer.
